You can use the MapStringUnionToObjectUnion type to map a string union type to an object union type, for example:

type MyStringUnion = 'foo' | 'bar' | 'baz';

type MyObjectUnion = MapStringUnionToObjectUnion<MyStringUnion>;

// MyObjectUnion is equivalent to:
// {value: 'foo'} | {value: 'bar'} | {value: 'baz'}
